Prepare this wonderful dish, using a pressure cooker, in 2 hours - honestly. Pressure cook Corned beef + spices + 2 cu water for 1 hr - remove and keep warm in oven. Check liquid in cooker - add whole potatoes, whole carrots, whole onions and cook for 7 min. Then add the quartered cabbage, parsnips, for 2 min. Wait for cooker to come up to pressure before timeing. Enjoy with lots of unsalted fresh butter! Happy Saint Patrick's Day!

