We have this every year. I serve it with horseradish gravy. I use 2 cups water from the pot{strained} and 1 chicken boullion. Heat in separate pan. Mix togather 1 packet chicken gravy mix and 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water until smooth. Whisk into water mixture. bring to a boil and then stir in 2 tablespoons prepared horseradish. Simmer 1-2 mins. Serve over potatoes, cabbage and meat. You can adjust horseradish to your own taste.

