Very good recipe. I agree with the cook from Belfast that this is unusual in Ireland, with boiled bacon (which is NOT like bacon in the USA!) being much more common. I was also surprised at the scarcity of seafood in the Republic. We were told it was the result of all the "Fish Fridays" when growing up. I add a little brown sugar and a 1/4 cup apple cider vinegar which seems to bring out the flavors a bit.

