Rating: 4
Fantastic!! Made this for the second year in a row...exceptional dish with no leftovers. As others recommended - added a bottle of beer after skimming off the foam 30 minutes into the simmering process. Made Lakeville, MI's (3/6/02) horseradish sauce: 'Whip 1 cup of heavy whipping cream until peaks form, fold in 1/4 cup horseradish sauce, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1 tbsp dijon mustard and bit of sugar.' Made Saratoga, CA's (3/16/01) to die for glaze: "took the beef out after 4 hours and put in a 400 oven for 30 minutes with the following glaze:kept the broth and cooked the carrots, potatoes and cabbage in it. Glaze: 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 3/4 cup apple juice, 3 tbs mustard and 3/4 cup bourbon." Simmer, simmer, simmer...don't boil. If you have problems trying to keep the water from boiling even on low, make a flame tamer: 3-ft. piece of foil crumpled into an "o" shape and put on your gas burner. It lifts the pot about 1/2" from the flame and helps keep the heat down. I won't wait another year to make this again.

