Rating: 3
This is a tremendously satisfying and delicious "comfort food" recipe. I'll definitely make this again in the fall and winter. I modified/updated this 1965 recipe a bit, just because I can never leave well enough alone in a recipe: 1. sear the meat to seal in juices, but don't season beforehand; 2. add a cup of white wine in place of one cup of water; 3. double up on the carrots, they add sweetness; 4. use both the 6 peppercorns and use 2 T. of the picking spice. 7. sit back and let the house start smelling great!

